snippet.title: Halloween - Official Announcement Trailer | gamescom2025
snippet.description:
Michael Myers Returns to Haddonfield. Check out the Halloween trailer for the upcoming asymmetric stealth horror game with single and multiplayer modes from developer and publisher IllFonic, co-published by Gun Interactive, and in partnership with Compass International Pictures and Further Front. Halloween will be available on Xbox Series X|S, PlayStation 5 (PS5), and PC via Steam and Epic Game Store in 2026.

Step into the chilling world of John Carpenter’s genre-defining film, now transformed into a suspenseful one-versus-many stealth horror experience in Halloween. Put on the iconic mask to become the ultimate slasher, Michael Myers, stalking and executing the citizens of Haddonfield one by one, or striving to thwart Michael Myers’ plans as Civilians determined to save the unaware townsfolk before it’s too late. 

Stick to the shadows as Civilians, seeking out Haddonfield residents to warn them and searching for a way to contact the authorities. As Michael Myers, give them a reason to fear the dark and cut the phone lines to prevent the police from ruining his favorite holiday.

#IGN #Gaming #gamescom2025

snippet.title: Sekiro: No Defeat | Official Trailer | Crunchyroll
snippet.description:
Sekiro: No Defeat is coming exclusively to Crunchyroll!

The time is Sengoku.

Japan is fractured into many independent nations entangled in ceaseless war. At the center lies Ashina, a land of sacred earth and ancient mystery. Two decades after Sword Saint Isshin Ashina reclaimed the region in a brutal coup, a new threat emerges from within: The Interior Ministry. Desperate to protect his homeland, Isshin’s grandson Genichiro turns to forbidden powers. The only hope lies in a kidnapped boy — the Divine Heir — and his silent protector: a loyal shinobi known only as Sekiro.

This is the story of a lord and his retainer — and their quest to restore balance to a nation on the edge.

Crunchyroll brings you the latest clips, openings, full episodes, and more from your favorite anime!

WATCH FULL EPISODES ON YOUTUBE 🌟 https://got.cr/cc-pt

Go for gold in the Grand Prix, challenge racers online in World Match, compete for the best time in Time Trial, and change up the rules and teams in Race Park!

snippet.title: Warhammer 40,000: Dawn of War IV Official Announce Trailer | Gamescom Opening Night 2025
snippet.description:
At last, back to war! Warhammer 40,000: Dawn of War IV officially revealed during Gamescom Opening Night Live 2025!

Battle for planet Kronus as Warhammer 40,000's ultimate real time strategy game returns, featuring the largest campaign ever with four distinct factions battling it out in epic, brutal large-scale conflicts. 

Dawn of War IV returns to the legendary RTS series’ roots with satisfying gameplay and a brutal, expanded Sync Kill system. Take command of four Warhammer 40,000 factions, including, for the first time in the Dawn of War series, the Adeptus Mechanicus! Fight through 70+ campaign missions solo or with a friend in a story crafted by legendary Black Library author John French. Immerse yourself in endlessly replayable modes including Last Stand and Skirmish, or take the fight to the world with intense multiplayer combat.

Read more on Warhammer Community: https://www.warhammer-community.com/en-gb/articles/l8pdgqps/warhammer-40000-dawn-of-war-iv/

Wishlist NOW on Steam: https://ow.ly/wPeP50WIbWb

snippet.description:
Official video for the new single “Drum Show” from the forthcoming album Breach, out September 12th. 

Pre-order / Pre-save Breach: https://top.lnk.to/breach
Stream/Download "Drum Show”: https://top.lnk.to/drumshow

THE CLANCY TOUR: BREACH 2025

OCT 25 - Los Angeles, CA @ BMO Stadium - SOLD OUT
OCT 26 - Los Angeles, CA @ BMO Stadium 

LYRICS
Putting on a drum show.
 
Completed checklist for today,
Now they have to let you out of your cage,
Feeling stuck between a rock and a home,
Two places you do not want to go, so, so.
 
He’s putting on a drum show,
Even now, even now,
He’ll take the longer way home,
Even now, even now,
He’ll never, ever say so,
He drives fast just to feel it, feel it,
He drives slow if his song’s not over,
Drown it out, drown it out.
 
He’d rather feel something than nothing at all,
So he swerves all around as his head starts to fall,
Turns it up,
Stuck between a rock and a home,
Two places he does not want to go, so, so.
 
I’ve been this way,
I want to change.

Yeah, uh-huh

Broke up with my girl last night so I went to the club (So I went to the club)
Put on a fresh white suit and the mini-coupe sittin' on dubs (Sittin' on dubs)
I'm just lookin' for somebody to talk to and show me some love (Show me some love)
If you know what I mean, uh-huh
Everybody jockin' me as soon as I stepped in the spot (I stepped in the spot)
Two hundred bi***es in the building, ain't none of them hot (Ain't none of them hot)
Except for this pretty young thang that was workin' on the way, at the top (On the way, at the top)
Shawty, what is your name?
[Pre-Chorus: T-Pain]
Ooh, she made us drinks to drink, we drunk 'em, got drunk
And I think she thinks I'm cool
She gave me a wink, I winked back, and then I think that
We hit it off somethin' proper like

[Chorus: T-Pain]
I like the bartender (Ooh, if you lookin' for me)
I'm at the bar with her (Oh oh oh uh-huh, okay)
I like the bartender (Yeah, if you lookin' for me)
I'm at the bar with her (Oh oh oh uh-huh, okay)

[Verse 2: T-Pain]
Got a brand new girl so I'm feelin' all good inside (All good inside)
Feel like I put some brand new twenty-fours on a brand new ride (On a brand new ride)
Triple shot of Patron on the rocks with a little bit of lime (With a little bit of lime)
I'm just keepin' it real, uh-huh
Baby still workin' at the club so I'm gettin' in free (So I'm gettin' in free)
Wednesday night, I'm on the list, T-Pain plus three (T-Pain plus three)
Every time I hit the spot babygirl takin' care of me (Takin' care of me)
How do you think I feel?

[Pre-Chorus: T-Pain]
Ooh, she made us drinks to drink, we drunk 'em, got drunk
And now I know she thinks I'm cool
She gave me a wink, I winked back, and then I think that
We gon' have fun at my spot tonight

[Chorus: T-Pain]
I like the bartender (Ooh, if you lookin' for me)
I'm at the bar with her (Oh oh oh uh-huh, okay)
I like the bartender (Yeah, if you lookin' for me)
I'm at the bar with her (Oh oh oh uh-huh, okay)

[Verse 3: Akon & T-Pain]
Shorty, I'm sure you heard that I rarely ever come out (Ever come out)
'Less I'm in the M6, doin' tricks, freeway burnt out (Freeway burnt out)
Got a passenger side that's empty wantin' it to be your spot (Be your stop)
Put you on my Billboard, we can act like the charts, I can end up on top (And I end up on top)
Don't smoke, don't drink, that's why I don't be by the bar baby (Baby)
Just lookin' at you from a distance, lookin' like a goddamn star baby (Baby)
So my girl don't see me T-Pain, can I get those keys to the car? (Those keys to the car)
'Bout to go and bang bang boogie with my cutie and I'll see you tomorrow (I'll see you tomorrow)

[Pre-Chorus: T-Pain & Akon]
Ooh, she made us drinks to drink, we drunk 'em, got drunk
And now I know, she thinks I'm cool (She thinks I'm cool)
She gave me a wink, I winked back (Uh-huh)
And then I think that (Uh-huh)
We gon' have fun at my spot tonight (Oh, yeah, slide)

[Chorus: T-Pain]
I like the bartender (Ooh, if you lookin' for me)
I'm at the bar with her (Oh oh oh uh-huh, okay)
I like the bartender (Yeah, if you lookin' for me)
I'm at the bar with her (Oh oh oh uh-huh, okay)

snippet.title: Honest Trailers | War of the Worlds (2025)
snippet.description:
It’s the Honest Trailer for War of the Worlds 2025! The version with Ice Cube, Eva Longoria, and all the apps you use to work from home! What would you do if aliens invaded and you were the only person who could stop it? A) Yell at your daughter for eating a muffin? B) spy on the Washington Monument C) Check Fox News or D) All of the above? People have been saying this one isn’t so bad it’s good, but we disagree, this is the most we’ve laughed at a film in years.

What would you like us to make an Honest Trailer for next?

Voice Narration: Jon Bailey the EPIC VOICE GUY (@epicvoiceguy on all socials)
Title Design: Robert Holtby 
Written by: Spencer Gilbert and Lon Harris
Produced by: Spencer Gilbert 
Edited by: Kevin Williamsen 
Post-Production Manager: Emin Bassavand 
Manager, Video Operations: Tiffany Tse 
Post-Production Specialist: Rebecca Castaneda 
VP Content: Max Dionne

snippet.title: The Morning Show — Season 4 Official Trailer | Apple TV+
snippet.description:
It’s not just a return. It’s a reckoning. The Morning Show Season 4 premieres September 17 on Apple TV+ https://apple.co/_TheMorningShow

The Morning Show stars and is executive produced by Jennifer Aniston and Reese Witherspoon, alongside showrunner and executive producer Charlotte Stoudt, and director and executive producer Mimi Leder. 
 
Season 4 of The Morning Show opens in spring 2024, almost two years after the events of Season 3. With the UBA-NBN merger complete, the newsroom must grapple with newfound responsibility, hidden motives and the elusive nature of truth in a polarized America. In a world rife with deepfakes, conspiracy theories and corporate cover-ups — who can you trust? And how can you know what’s actually real? Along with Witherspoon and Aniston, the star-studded Season 4 ensemble cast includes Billy Crudup, Karen Pittman, Nicole Beharie, Nestor Carbonell, Mark Duplass, Greta Lee, Marion Cotillard, Jeremy Irons, Aaron Pierre, William Jackson Harper, Boyd Holbrook, and Jon Hamm.
 
The drama is showrun and executive produced by Stoudt, and directed and executive produced by Leder. The series is produced by the studio Media Res, and executive produced by Michael Ellenberg and Lindsey Springer through Media Res, along with Stoudt and Leder. Aniston and Kristin Hahn executive produce through Echo Films, while Witherspoon executive produces alongside Lauren Neustadter for Hello Sunshine. Zander Lehmann and Micah Schraft also executive produce.

Song: “Castle” by Halsey https://apple.co/Castle_Halsey

en.title: The Morning Show — Season 4 Official Trailer | Apple TV+
en.description:
It’s not just a return. It’s a reckoning. The Morning Show Season 4 premieres September 17 on Apple TV+ https://apple.co/_TheMorningShow

The Morning Show stars and is executive produced by Jennifer Aniston and Reese Witherspoon, alongside showrunner and executive producer Charlotte Stoudt, and director and executive producer Mimi Leder. 
 
Season 4 of The Morning Show opens in spring 2024, almost two years after the events of Season 3. With the UBA-NBN merger complete, the newsroom must grapple with newfound responsibility, hidden motives and the elusive nature of truth in a polarized America. In a world rife with deepfakes, conspiracy theories and corporate cover-ups — who can you trust? And how can you know what’s actually real? Along with Witherspoon and Aniston, the star-studded Season 4 ensemble cast includes Billy Crudup, Karen Pittman, Nicole Beharie, Nestor Carbonell, Mark Duplass, Greta Lee, Marion Cotillard, Jeremy Irons, Aaron Pierre, William Jackson Harper, Boyd Holbrook, and Jon Hamm.
 
The drama is showrun and executive produced by Stoudt, and directed and executive produced by Leder. The series is produced by the studio Media Res, and executive produced by Michael Ellenberg and Lindsey Springer through Media Res, along with Stoudt and Leder. Aniston and Kristin Hahn executive produce through Echo Films, while Witherspoon executive produces alongside Lauren Neustadter for Hello Sunshine. Zander Lehmann and Micah Schraft also executive produce.

snippet.description:
Anniversary - Watch the trailer now! In theaters October 29. Starring Diane Lane, Kyle Chandler, Madeline Brewer, Zoey Deutch, Phoebe Dynevor, Mckenna Grace, Daryl McCormack, and Dylan O’Brien. 

Subscribe to the LIONSGATE: YouTube Channel for the latest movie trailers, clips, and more: https://bit.ly/2Z6nfym

https://www.facebook.com/lionsgate

https://www.instagram.com/lionsgate/
https://www.tiktok.com/@lionsgate

 #AnniversaryMovie

In this gripping thriller, a close-knit family is caught in the turmoil of a controversial rising movement known as “The Change.” Ellen and Paul (Diane Lane and Kyle Chandler) witness their lives fall apart when Ellen’s former student Liz (Phoebe Dynevor) reappears and starts dating their son (Dylan O’Brien). As Liz becomes a part of the Taylor family, tensions rise and loyalties are tested. Liz’s role in “The Change” brings simmering conflicts to the surface, unraveling the fabric of the family just as the nation itself stands on edge during an alarming and challenging time of uncertainty.

snippet.title: Zach Top - South Of Sanity
snippet.description:
The official visualizer for Zach Top's single "South Of Sanity" from the highly anticipated album Ain't In It For My Health. Available now: https://leo33.lnk.to/southofsanityyt

Ain't In It For My Health: https://leo33.lnk.to/aintinitformyhealthyt

Connect with Zach Top:
https://zachtop.os.fan
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/zachtop/
TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@zachtop
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/zachtopmusic/
Official Website: https://www.zachtop.com/

Lyrics:
Playin' a rodeo in Montana tonight
She's two thousand miles away
Says she loves me on the phone as she cries
Wishes I’d come home to stay
 
But I’m somewhere outside of Missoula 
They just called my name from the stage
When we hung up she was talkin' leavin'
Now how am I supposed to sing and play
She's left me somewhere south of sanity 
Still just north of insane
 
The show is over I tried twice to call her back
But no answer either time
My thoughts are racin' like a fast car 'round the track
Aw and I can't get her off my mind
 
And I'm somewhere outside Albuquerque
They just called my name from the stage
When we last talked she was talkin' leavin'
Now how am I supposed to sing and play
She's left me somewhere south of sanity 
Still just north of 
 
Startin' to believe I might be losin' everything
 
Still I’m somewhere outside Amarillo
They just called my name from the stage
When we last talked she was talkin' leavin'
But I gotta show I gotta play
Somewhere south of sanity 
Still just north of insane

Written by Zach Top, Carson Chamberlain and Mark Nesler

Credits:
Carson Chamberlain (Producer)
Matt Rovey (Recording Engineer)
Will Kienzle (Assistant Engineer)
Matt Rovey (Mixer)
Ken Love (Mastering Engineer)

Gary Prim (Piano/Keys)
Zach Top (Vocals/Background Vocals)

Recorded at Sound Stage Studios in Nashville, TN
Mixed at Sound Stage Studios in Nashville, TN
Mastered at Five Points Mastering in Nashville, TN

snippet.title: KISS OF THE SPIDER WOMAN | Official Trailer | In Theaters October 10
snippet.description:
DREAMGIRLS and BEAUTY AND THE BEAST director Bill Condon returns to the movie musical in this dazzling Technicolor-hued fantasy.  Valentín (Diego Luna), a political prisoner, shares a cell with Molina (Tonatiuh), a window dresser convicted of public indecency. The two form an unlikely bond as Molina recounts the plot of a Hollywood musical starring his favorite silver screen diva, Ingrid Luna (Jennifer Lopez).   Based on the Tony Award-winning Broadway musical hit.
 
Bill Condon’s  visionary new adaptation is based on the acclaimed 1976 novel Kiss of the Spider Woman by Argentinian writer Manuel Puig and the Tony Award®-winning Broadway musical of the same name by the multiple Tony Award®-winning playwright Terrence McNally (Master Class, Ragtime) and composer/lyricist team John Kander and Fred Ebb (Cabaret, Chicago). Written for the screen and directed by Bill Condon, this visually stunning and emotionally charged adaptation stars Emmy Award® nominee Diego Luna (Andor, Y tu mamá también), Tonatiuh (Carry On, Promised Land), and Emmy® and Grammy® Award-nominated superstar Jennifer Lopez (Hustlers, Out of Sight), who also serves as an executive producer alongside Diego Luna. Produced by Barry Josephson, p.g.a., Tom Kirdahy, p.g.a., and Greg Yolen, p.g.a

#KissoftheSpiderWoman
https://www.kissofthespiderwomanfilm.com/

snippet.title: RESIDENT EVIL 9 REQUIEM Gameplay Demo (No Commentary)
snippet.description:
RESIDENT EVIL REQUIEM Gameplay Demo (No Commentary)

Resident Evil Requiem, the ninth and most immersive mainline entry yet in the iconic survival horror Resident Evil™ series, will launch on February 27, 2026, across PlayStation®5, Xbox Series X|S, and PC via Steam. Powered by RE ENGINE and harnessing the full power of modern consoles, Resident Evil Requiem delivers spine-chilling realism like never before, with complex character details like lifelike facial expressions, realistic skin textures, and even high-fidelity sweat droplets that are sure to keep players on the edge of their seats. Resident Evil Requiem takes the series back to the iconic Raccoon City, home of the biological disaster that shook the world, combining deeply terrifying aspects of psychological horror with pulse-pounding action that franchise fans know and love.

Wishlist the game here:
https://store.steampowered.com/app/3764200/Resident_Evil_Requiem/

0:00 - Intro Cutscene
3:30 - First Person Gameplay
12:18 - Third Person Gameplay

snippet.description:

You must survive 99 nights in the forest, where monsters become stronger with every passing night. Gather resources, craft tools, and stay alive as the woods grow darker and more dangerous. Only the strongest will endure all 99. 🌲🦉🔥

#roblox #bloxboysoriginal #gamingmusic #99nightsintheforest #robloxmusic #forestmonsters #robloxhorror #bloxboysoriginal #survivalmusic #nightchallenge #robloxupdate

CREDITS:
Animation ►  @memeycorny7773  
Vocals ► @n3onine
Prod ► @NotiniRBLX

- --- -----Lyrics -- --- --- -- -
Night one, still feeling brave,
Night two, I’m digging my grave.
By night three, I’ve learned the sound
Of footsteps that don’t touch the ground.

Campfire’s low, my hands are numb,
Every shadow asksing me to come.
The trees lean close like they all know
Where I’ll be buried when I go.

Ninety-nine nights, no sunrise here,
No one comes, no help appears.
We run, we hide, we scream, we fight,
Through ninety-nine nights of endless night.

Some kids vanish, some kids stay,
Some kids laugh ‘cause they’ve gone insane.
Whispers in the dark, pulling at my sleeve,
Telling me lies I almost believe.

The deer’s not the only thing out here—
There’s voices, claws and things unclear.
Some nights feel like they never end,
Some nights eat your only friend.

Ninety-nine nights, no sunrise here,
No one comes, no help appears.
We run, we hide, we scream, we fight,
Through ninety-nine nights of endless night.

They say if you make it, you get to leave,
But I don’t trust what they want me to believe.
What if the game just starts again
With new kids trapped where I have been.

Ninety-nine nights, no sunrise here,
No one comes, no help appears.
We run, we hide, we scream, we fight,
Through ninety-nine nights of endless night.

Night two, I’m digging my grave.
By night three, I’ve learned the sound
Of footsteps that don’t touch the ground.

Campfire’s low, my hands are numb,
Every shadow asksing me to come.
The trees lean close like they all know
Where I’ll be buried when I go.

Ninety-nine nights, no sunrise here,
No one comes, no help appears.
We run, we hide, we scream, we fight,
Through ninety-nine nights of endless night.

Some kids vanish, some kids stay,
Some kids laugh ‘cause they’ve gone insane.
Whispers in the dark, pulling at my sleeve,
Telling me lies I almost believe.

The deer’s not the only thing out here—
There’s voices, claws and things unclear.
Some nights feel like they never end,
Some nights eat your only friend.

Ninety-nine nights, no sunrise here,
No one comes, no help appears.
We run, we hide, we scream, we fight,
Through ninety-nine nights of endless night.

They say if you make it, you get to leave,
But I don’t trust what they want me to believe.
What if the game just starts again
With new kids trapped where I have been.

No one comes, no help appears.
We run, we hide, we scream, we fight,
Through ninety-nine nights of endless night.

de-DE.description:
Ich bin gerade über meine alte Minecraft-Welt von vor 12 Jahren gestolpert … und sie ist der Wahnsinn! Von meinen allerersten Noob-Builds bis hin zu geheimen Basen, die ich völlig vergessen hatte – diese Welt ist wie eine Zeitkapsel meiner Kindheit!

#johnny #minecraft #minecraftmod

nl-NL.title: Ik heb mijn OUDE GEHEIME Minecraft-wereld van 12 jaar geleden gevonden!
nl-NL.description:
Ik stuitte zojuist op mijn oude Minecraft-wereld van 12 jaar geleden... en hij is GEWELDIG! Van mijn allereerste noob-builds tot geheime bases die ik helemaal vergeten was, deze wereld is als een tijdcapsule uit mijn jeugd!

#johnny #minecraft #minecraftmod

hi.title: मुझे 12 साल पहले का मेरा पुराना गुप्त Minecraft World मिल गया!
hi.description:
मैं अभी-अभी अपने 12 साल पुराने Minecraft वर्ल्ड पर अचानक से नज़र दौड़ा आया... और ये वाकई कमाल का है! मेरे शुरुआती नौसिखिए बिल्ड से लेकर उन गुप्त ठिकानों तक, जिन्हें मैं पूरी तरह भूल गया था, ये दुनिया मेरे बचपन के टाइम कैप्सूल जैसी है!

#johnny #minecraft #minecraftmod

pl.title: Odkryłem mój STARY, TAJEMNICZY świat Minecrafta sprzed 12 lat!
pl.description:
Właśnie natknąłem się na mój stary świat Minecrafta sprzed 12 lat… i jest NIESAMOWITY! Od moich pierwszych, nowicjuszowskich konstrukcji po sekretne bazy, o których kompletnie zapomniałem – ten świat jest jak kapsuła czasu z mojego dzieciństwa!

#johnny #minecraft #minecraftmod

fr-FR.title: J'ai retrouvé mon vieux monde Minecraft SECRET d'il y a 12 ans !
fr-FR.description:
Je viens de redécouvrir mon ancien monde Minecraft d'il y a 12 ans… et c'est dingue ! De mes toutes premières constructions de débutant aux bases secrètes que j'avais complètement oubliées, ce monde est comme une capsule temporelle de mon enfance !

#johnny #minecraft #minecraftmod

ko.title: 12년 전의 비밀스러운 마인크래프트 세계를 찾았습니다!
ko.description:
12년 전 제 옛 마인크래프트 세계를 우연히 발견했는데… 정말 끝내줘요! 제 첫 초보 빌드부터 완전히 잊고 있던 비밀 기지까지, 이 세계는 마치 제 어린 시절의 타임캡슐 같아요!

#johnny #minecraft #minecraftmod

it.title: Ho trovato il mio VECCHIO mondo SEGRETO di Minecraft di 12 anni fa!
it.description:
Mi sono appena imbattuto nel mio vecchio mondo di Minecraft di 12 anni fa... ed è FOLLE! Dalle mie primissime build da principiante alle basi segrete di cui mi ero completamente dimenticato, questo mondo è come una capsula del tempo della mia infanzia!

#johnny #minecraft #minecraftmod

ja.title: 12 年前の古い秘密の Minecraft ワールドを発見しました!
ja.description:
12年前のMinecraftワールドを偶然見つけたんだけど… めちゃくちゃすごい！ 初めての初心者向け作品からすっかり忘れてた秘密基地まで、このワールドはまるで子供時代のタイムカプセルみたい！

#johnny #minecraft #minecraftmod

pt-BR.title: Encontrei meu ANTIGO mundo SECRETO do Minecraft de 12 anos atrás!
pt-BR.description:
Acabei de me deparar com meu antigo mundo do Minecraft de 12 anos atrás... e é INSANO! Das minhas primeiras construções de noob até bases secretas que eu esqueci completamente, este mundo é como uma cápsula do tempo da minha infância!

#johnny #minecraft #minecraftmod

id.title: Saya Menemukan Dunia Minecraft RAHASIA LAMA Saya Dari 12 Tahun Lalu!
id.description:
Aku baru saja menemukan dunia Minecraft lamaku dari 12 tahun yang lalu... dan itu GILA! Dari build-ku yang masih pemula hingga markas-markas rahasia yang benar-benar kulupakan, dunia ini seperti kapsul waktu masa kecilku!

#johnny #minecraft #minecraftmod

es-US.title: ¡Encontré mi VIEJO mundo SECRETO de Minecraft de hace 12 años!
es-US.description:
Me topé con mi antiguo mundo de Minecraft de hace 12 años… ¡y es una locura! Desde mis primeras construcciones de novato hasta bases secretas que había olvidado por completo, ¡este mundo es como una cápsula del tiempo de mi infancia!

#johnny #minecraft #minecraftmod

📃Letra/Lyrics:

¿Qué me hizo usted?
Que la quiero Volver a ver
Y volverla a besar
Yo te paso a buscar, buscar…

Es que la bellaquera contigo
Con nadie mas la consigo
De tus gritos no me olvido, oh - oh

Tengo reservado el hotel,
Pero con estas ganas no vamo’ a llegar
Somos dos desesperados por eso nos tuvimos que parkear
Atras nos espera el asiento
Tu eres una Aventura
Cuando te desnudas 

Tengo reservado el hotel,
Pero con estas ganas no vamo’ a llegar
Somos dos desesperados por eso nos tuvimos que parkear
Atras nos espera el asiento
Tu eres una Aventura
Cuando te desnudas 

Las ganas de tenerla
Yo no pude, tuve
Que Aceptarlo cuando me detuve, sudé
En la parte de atrás 
Aunque falta comodidad
Tus gritos confirmaron que has visto las nubes
La bellaquera nos domina 
Siempre que tu y yo nos vemos 
No importa el ambiente, donde sea nos comemos
No hay planificación 
Porque a ti la situación te descontrola 
Y no hay forma de evitar la situación 
Siempre terminamos sin ropa
No te conformas con un beso en la boca
Según tu dices, yo soy el que te provoca
Pero me buscas, aunque sabes que tengo a otra

Tengo reservado el hotel,
Pero con estas ganas no vamos a llegar
Somos dos desesperados por eso nos tuvimos que marchar
Atras nos espera el asiento
Tu eres una Aventura
Cuando te desnudas 

La primera vez que perriamos
No pudimos evitarlo y nos besamos
Que el momento no acabara
No dejamo’ en vano
No fue, la toqué como un piano
Tu mirada me dijo que estoy gano
¿Mami, tu quieres mas?
¿Tu quieres mas?
¿Tu quieres mas?
Bebé, pues no se hable mas
No me sueltes y vámonos de una vez
Bendecido por ser el que ve tu desnudez
Lo mas que me gusta de ti es tu sencillez
Le gusta agresivo, pero que entre con delicadez
De la Metro a Mayagüez

¿Que me dice usted?
Que la quiero Volver a ver
Y volverla a besar
Yo te paso a buscar, buscar….

Es que la bellaquera contigo
Con nadie mas la consigo
De tus gritos no me olvido

Tengo reservado el hotel,
Pero con estas ganas no vamos a llegar
Somos dos desesperados por eso nos tuvimos que parkear
Atras nos espera el asiento
Tu eres una Aventura
Cuando te desnudas

snippet.title: Blackberry Smoke - Run With The Pack (feat. Paul Rodgers and Brann Dailor) (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Watch the official music video for Blackberry Smoke's rendition of "Run With The Pack" featuring Paul Rodgers and Brann Dailor.

Stream “Run With The Pack”: https://found.ee/runwiththepack
Pre-Order + Pre-Save CAN’T GET ENOUGH: A TRIBUTE TO BAD COMPANY: https://found.ee/badcompanytribute
 
Torchbearers of southern rock, Blackberry Smoke has released their rendition of the Bad Company classic, “Run with the Pack”, from the forthcoming tribute album, Can’t Get Enough: A Tribute to Bad Company, to be released October 24, 2025 on Primary Wave Music.  Bad Company co-founder and vocalist Paul Rodgers contributes background vocals on the track, while Brann Dailor of Mastodon plays percussion and also provides background vocals. 

“Bad Company has always been one of those bands that just hits you in the chest – raw, soulful and real,” says Charlie Starr of Blackberry Smoke. “Run with the Pack” is like a masterclass in groove and grit. There’s simplicity to it that’s so powerful – no frills, just feel. You don’t need to dress it up – it’s just honest. Paul Rodgers’ voice is cool confidence, never overdone, just authentic. That kind of music doesn’t age; it just gets cooler.”

Paul Rodgers says, “Blackberry Smoke absolutely channeled the essence of the song and everyone delivered from their souls. I love every aspect of their performance harmonies, guitars and delivery!”

Director & Editor: Andy Sapp (Freedom Machine)
Recorded and Mixed by Tom Tapley at West End Sound
Additional Engineering: Miles Landrum
Song published and album released: https://PrimaryWave.com/

Written by Paul Rodgers
Published by Badco Music Inc. (ASCAP) and WC Music Corp. (ASCAP)
All rights administered by WC Music Corp.
Charlie Starr (Lead Vocal & Guitar), Kent Aberle (Drums), Richard Turner (Bass), Paul Jackson (Guitar), Benji Shanks (Guitar), Brandon Still (Piano)
Background Vocals – Charlie Starr, Paul Rodgers, Paul Jackson, Brann Dailor
Percussion – Brann Dailor
Recording & Mixing by Tom Tapley at West End Sound (Atlanta, GA)
Additional Engineering – Miles Landrum
Brann Dailor appears courtesy of Loma Vista Recordings

Lyrics:
You never give me my money
You only give me your sympathy
'Cause I keep on running
There ain’t no way to catch up with me
I'm leaving you, don't make no fuss
You won't even see me, oh no, for dust

I'm running with the pack
I’m running with the pack
I'm running with the pack
Never looking back.
 
You try to keep me in cages
But baby, you got to catch me first
You think your law is contagious
I'll do my best, you can do your worst
I'm leaving you, now who can I trust
You won't even see me, oh no, for dust
 
I'm running with the pack
I’m running with the pack
I'm running with the pack
Never looking back

#BlackberrySmoke #BadCompany #RunWithThePack

“Bad Company has always been one of those bands that just hits you in the chest – raw, soulful and real,” says Charlie Starr of Blackberry Smoke. “Run with the Pack” is like a masterclass in groove and grit. There’s simplicity to it that’s so powerful – no frills, just feel. You don’t need to dress it up – it’s just honest. Paul Rodgers’ voice is cool confidence, never overdone, just authentic. That kind of music doesn’t age; it just gets cooler.”

Paul Rodgers says, “Blackberry Smoke absolutely channeled the essence of the song and everyone delivered from their souls. I love every aspect of their performance harmonies, guitars and delivery!”

Director & Editor: Andy Sapp (Freedom Machine)
Recorded and Mixed by Tom Tapley at West End Sound
Additional Engineering: Miles Landrum
Song published and album released: https://PrimaryWave.com/

Written by Paul Rodgers
Published by Badco Music Inc. (ASCAP) and WC Music Corp. (ASCAP)
All rights administered by WC Music Corp.
Charlie Starr (Lead Vocal & Guitar), Kent Aberle (Drums), Richard Turner (Bass), Paul Jackson (Guitar), Benji Shanks (Guitar), Brandon Still (Piano)
Background Vocals – Charlie Starr, Paul Rodgers, Paul Jackson, Brann Dailor
Percussion – Brann Dailor
Recording & Mixing by Tom Tapley at West End Sound (Atlanta, GA)
Additional Engineering – Miles Landrum
Brann Dailor appears courtesy of Loma Vista Recordings

snippet.title: RESIDENT EVIL 9 REQUIEM Exclusive Gamescom 2025 Demo | Best ZOMBIE SURVIVAL HORROR coming in 2026
snippet.description:
Check out the first exclusive preview demo look at the upcoming Resident Evil Requiem running in RE Engine. We captured this gameplay footage in a PlayStation 5 Pro at a exclusive event prior to Gamescom 2025 (no commentary). This is the new entry of the popular single player survival horror shooter with zombies, inventory management and puzzles!

First Impressions:

Playing Resident Evil Requiem for the first time has been a wild ride, and the previews we read beforehand definitely set the stage perfectly. Capcom has truly gone back to the series' survival horror roots, which feels amazing. You play as Grace Ashcroft, a young FBI technical analyst who is also the daughter of Alyssa Ashcroft, the investigative reporter from Resident Evil Outbreak. The game's atmosphere reminds us a lot of Resident Evil 7, with its terrifying first person sections and claustrophobic corridors. But what's really cool is that you can switch from first person to third person at the menu anytime, which offers a totally different way to experience the scares.

The classic Resident Evil formula is all here: you have to solve puzzles to advance, finding keys, fuses, and screwdrivers to open up new areas. Resource management is key, and we were thrilled to see that green herbs are back for healing. You're not always armed, and a lot of the initial gameplay involves stealth and using your environment, like throwing bottles to distract enemies. This is crucial because, just like Mr. X or Lady Dimitrescu, there’s a giant monster chasing you that feels smarter and more relentless than ever. One of the best things we saw in the demo was how the monster’s pursuit now takes place on different vertical levels, and it can appear at any moment from the ceiling, adding a whole new layer of terror. The demo we played was incredibly dark, so we had to use my lighter a lot, which made the entire experience even more suffocating as we could barely see anything and always felt the monster was close by. Thankfully, based on the rumors, it seems Grace isn't the only protagonist. There's another well-known main character with lots of weapons who reportedly shows up later on. We can't wait to see how that changes the dynamic. It's shaping up to be a true return to form for the series, and we've got my calendar marked for its release on 2026!

Coming 27 February, 2026 to PS5, Xbox and PC https://store.steampowered.com/app/3764200/Resident_Evil_Requiem/

Brettski strutted across the parking lot of Gate City Casino, the flicker of neon bouncing off his mirrored sunglasses. It was his first visit since they’d scrapped the betting limits on table games, and he could feel the change in the air—tense, electric, like the moments before a summer storm.

Inside, the place throbbed with energy. High rollers in tailored suits sipped bourbon next to college kids in backwards hats. Brettski beelined to the blackjack table, where the dealer, a woman with a silver streak in her hair and a poker face carved from stone, nodded once. He threw down a crisp ten grand.

"Hit me," he said.

Ace.

"Again."

Nine.

"Stay."

The dealer flipped. Twenty. Push.

A warm-up.

He escalated. Twenty grand. Fifty. Soon, the whole table watched as Brettski’s pile of chips grew like a small mountain. Rumors started flying—he was an ex-pro, an MIT card counter, a guy who once won a Corvette on a single spin.

He switched to roulette, dropped \$100,000 on black. The ball spun. Red.

No flinch. He doubled it. Black again. Red again.

The crowd hushed. Then he slid his entire bankroll across the felt.

“One million. On seventeen.”

Gasps.

The croupier swallowed hard. The ball spun.

“Come on, lucky number seventeen...” Brettski whispered.

The wheel slowed. Click-click-click... seventeen. The place exploded.

Before he could celebrate, two security guards flanked him. A third handed him a phone.

“Someone wants to speak with you,” the guard said grimly.

Brettski frowned. “Who?”

A gravelly voice on the other end: *“I told you never to gamble again, Brett. You just triggered the contract.”*

“What contract?”

But the line went dead. The lights flickered. The dealer was gone. The chips vanished.

And all around him, the casino fell silent.

Brettski se pavanait sur le parking du Gate City Casino, les reflets des néons se reflétant sur ses lunettes de soleil miroir. C'était sa première visite depuis l'abolition des limites de mise aux jeux de table, et il sentait le changement dans l'air : une tension électrique, comme avant un orage d'été.

À l'intérieur, l'ambiance vibrait d'énergie. Des flambeurs en costumes sur mesure sirotaient du bourbon aux côtés d'étudiants coiffés de chapeaux à l'envers. Brettski se dirigea droit vers la table de blackjack, où la croupière, une femme aux cheveux argentés et au visage impassible sculpté dans la pierre, acquiesça d'un signe de tête. Il jeta dix mille jetons impeccables.

« Frappe-moi », dit-il.

As.

« Encore. »

Neuf.

« Reste. »

Le croupier retourna. Vingt. Pousser.

Un échauffement.

Il s'emballa. Vingt mille. Cinquante. Bientôt, toute la table vit la pile de jetons de Brettski grossir comme une petite montagne. Les rumeurs commencèrent à circuler : c'était un ancien pro, un compteur de cartes du MIT, un type qui avait un jour gagné une Corvette en un seul tour.

Il passa à la roulette et déposa 100 000 $ sur le noir. La bille tourna. Rouge.

Sans broncher. Il doubla la mise. De nouveau noir. De nouveau rouge.

La foule se tut. Puis il fit glisser toute sa mise sur le tapis.

« Un million. Sur le dix-sept. »

Halètements.

Le croupier déglutit difficilement. La bille tourna.

« Allez, numéro porte-bonheur dix-sept… » chuchota Brettski.

La roue ralentit. Clic-clic-clic… dix-sept. La salle explosa.

Avant qu'il puisse célébrer, deux agents de sécurité l'entourèrent. Un troisième lui tendit un téléphone.

« Quelqu'un souhaite vous parler », dit l'agent d'un ton sombre.

Brettski fronça les sourcils. « Qui ? »

Une voix rauque à l'autre bout du fil : *« Je t'avais dit de ne plus jamais jouer, Brett. Tu as simplement déclenché le contrat. »*

« Quel contrat ? »

Mais la ligne fut coupée. Les lumières vacillèrent. Le croupier avait disparu. Les jetons disparurent.

Et tout autour de lui, le silence retomba sur le casino.

Brettski attraversava impettito il parcheggio del Gate City Casino, con il bagliore del neon che rimbalzava sui suoi occhiali da sole a specchio. Era la sua prima visita da quando avevano abolito i limiti di puntata sui giochi da tavolo, e sentiva il cambiamento nell'aria: teso, elettrico, come gli istanti prima di un temporale estivo.

All'interno, il posto pulsava di energia. Grandi scommettitori in abiti su misura sorseggiavano bourbon accanto a studenti universitari con cappelli al contrario. Brettski si diresse verso il tavolo del blackjack, dove il dealer, una donna con una ciocca argentata tra i capelli e una faccia da poker scolpita nella pietra, annuì una volta. Gettò diecimila dollari.

"Carica", disse.

Asso.

"Ancora."

Nove.

"Resta."

Il dealer girò. Venti. Spingi.

Un riscaldamento.

Aumentò. Ventimila. Cinquanta. Presto, l'intero tavolo guardò la pila di fiches di Brettski crescere come una piccola montagna. Cominciarono a circolare voci: era un ex professionista, un contatore di carte del MIT, uno che una volta aveva vinto una Corvette con un solo giro.

Passò alla roulette, scommise 100.000 dollari sul nero. La pallina girò. Rosso.

Senza battere ciglio. Raddoppiò. Di nuovo nero. Di nuovo rosso.

La folla tacque. Poi fece scivolare l'intero bankroll sul tappeto.

"Un milione. Sul diciassette."

Sobbalzi.

Il croupier deglutì a fatica. La pallina girò.

"Dai, numero fortunato diciassette..." sussurrò Brettski.

La ruota rallentò. Clic-clic-clic... diciassette. Il locale esplose.

Prima che potesse festeggiare, due guardie di sicurezza lo affiancarono. Una terza gli porse un telefono.

"Qualcuno vuole parlarti", disse la guardia cupamente.

Brettski aggrottò la fronte. "Chi?"

Una voce roca dall'altra parte: *"Ti avevo detto di non giocare mai più, Brett. Hai appena attivato il contratto."*

"Quale contratto?"

Ma la linea cadde. Le luci tremolarono. Il croupier se ne andò. Le fiches svanirono.

E tutto intorno a lui, il casinò piombò nel silenzio.

हम कैसीनो में वापस आकर मेरे लिए कुछ खास कर रहे हैं। गेट सिटी कैसीनो ने आखिरकार टेबल गेम्स पर अपनी छोटी-सी सीमा हटा दी है... तो समझ लीजिए कि अब आग लगाने का समय आ गया है! लाइक करने, सब्सक्राइब करने और कमेंट्स में अपने विचार देने के लिए आप सभी का बहुत-बहुत शुक्रिया। भले ही आप मुझे चिढ़ा रहे हों—मैं फिर भी आपसे प्यार करता हूँ। आप सभी बहुत खूबसूरत हैं, और इस रोमांचक सफ़र में साथ चलने के लिए मैं आप सभी का तहे दिल से शुक्रिया अदा करता हूँ। मुझे शुभकामनाएँ दें, और मैं आपसे अगले वीडियो में मिलूँगा! चलो जंग शुरू करते हैं।
खाली।

अगर आप स्लॉट और टेबल गेम बिल्कुल मुफ़्त और 40 से ज़्यादा राज्यों में खेलना चाहते हैं, तो नीचे दिए गए इस लिंक पर क्लिक करें और आज ही स्पिन क्वेस्ट पर खेलें। या लाइव स्ट्रीम देखें। मैं ज़्यादातर हफ़्ते के दिनों में स्पिन क्वेस्ट पर लाइव रहता हूँ! https://spinquest.com/?u=brettski

ब्रेट्स्की गेट सिटी कैसीनो की पार्किंग में इठलाते हुए चल रहे थे, उनके शीशे वाले धूप के चश्मे से नियॉन की चमक झिलमिला रही थी। टेबल गेम्स पर सट्टेबाज़ी की सीमा खत्म होने के बाद से यह उसकी पहली मुलाक़ात थी, और वह हवा में बदलाव महसूस कर सकता था—तनावपूर्ण, बिजली जैसा, जैसे गर्मी के तूफ़ान से पहले के पल।

अंदर, जगह ऊर्जा से भरी हुई थी। सिलवाए हुए सूट पहने बड़े-बड़े लोग उल्टी टोपी पहने कॉलेज के बच्चों के बगल में बोरबॉन की चुस्कियाँ ले रहे थे। ब्रेट्स्की सीधा ब्लैकजैक टेबल की ओर बढ़ा, जहाँ डीलर, बालों में चाँदी की लकीर और पत्थर से उकेरे गए पोकर चेहरे वाली एक महिला, ने एक बार सिर हिलाया। उसने दस हज़ार डॉलर फेंके।

"मुझे मारो," उसने कहा।

इक्का।

"फिर से।"

नौ।

"रुको।"

डीलर ने पलटी मारी। बीस। धक्का।

एक वार्म-अप।

उसने आगे बढ़ाया। बीस हज़ार। पचास। जल्द ही, पूरी टेबल ने देखा कि ब्रेट्स्की के चिप्स का ढेर एक छोटे पहाड़ की तरह बढ़ गया। अफ़वाहें उड़ने लगीं—वह एक पूर्व पेशेवर खिलाड़ी था, एमआईटी का कार्ड काउंटर, एक ऐसा व्यक्ति जिसने एक बार एक ही बार में कार्वेट जीत ली थी।

उसने रूलेट खेला, काले पर $100,000 डाले। गेंद घूमी। लाल।

बिना किसी हिचकिचाहट के। उसने उसे दोगुना कर दिया। फिर से काला। फिर से लाल।

भीड़ चुप हो गई। फिर उसने अपना पूरा बैंकरोल फ़ेल्ट पर सरका दिया।

"एक मिलियन। सत्रह पर।"

हाँफते हुए।

क्रुपियर ने मुश्किल से निगला। गेंद घूम गई।

"चलो, भाग्यशाली अंक सत्रह..." ब्रेट्स्की फुसफुसाया।

पहिया धीमा हो गया। क्लिक-क्लिक-क्लिक... सत्रह। जगह में धमाका हो गया।

इससे पहले कि वह जश्न मना पाता, दो सुरक्षा गार्ड उसके पास आ खड़े हुए। तीसरे ने उसे एक फ़ोन दिया।

"कोई तुमसे बात करना चाहता है," गार्ड ने गंभीरता से कहा।

ब्रेट्स्की ने भौंहें चढ़ाईं। "कौन?"

दूसरी तरफ़ से एक कर्कश आवाज़: *“मैंने तुमसे कहा था कि ब्रेट, फिर कभी जुआ मत खेलना। तुमने तो बस कॉन्ट्रैक्ट शुरू कर दिया।”*

“कौन सा कॉन्ट्रैक्ट?”

लेकिन लाइन बंद हो गई। लाइटें टिमटिमा गईं। डीलर चला गया। चिप्स गायब हो गए।

और उसके चारों ओर, कैसीनो में सन्नाटा छा गया।

#स्लॉट #ब्लैकजैक #जुआ #कैसीनो #बैकारेट #रूलेट

비어 있음.

슬롯머신과 테이블 게임을 완전 무료로 즐기고 싶으시다면, 40개 주 이상에서 오늘 Spin Quest에서 플레이하세요. 아니면 라이브 스트리밍도 시청하세요. 저는 거의 평일에 Spin Quest에서 생방송을 합니다! https://spinquest.com/?u=brettski

Brettski는 Gate City Casino 주차장을 활보하며 걸어갔고, 그의 미러 선글라스에 반짝이는 네온 불빛이 반짝였습니다. 테이블 게임의 베팅 한도가 폐지된 이후 처음 방문한 자리라 공기가 팽팽하게 긴장되고 짜릿한 기운으로 뒤덮인 것을 느낄 수 있었다. 마치 여름 폭풍이 몰아치기 직전처럼.

안은 활기로 가득했다. 맞춤 정장을 입은 하이롤러들이 모자를 거꾸로 쓴 대학생들 옆에서 버번 위스키를 홀짝였다. 브렛스키는 블랙잭 테이블로 곧장 향했다. 은색 머리카락에 돌로 조각한 포커페이스를 한 여자 딜러가 고개를 한 번 끄덕였다. 그는 빳빳한 1만 달러짜리 카드를 내밀었다.

"쳐 봐." 그가 말했다.

에이스.

"다시."

9.

"멈춰."

딜러가 카드를 뒤집었다. 20. 푸시.

워밍업.

그는 카드를 올렸다. 2만 달러. 50. 곧 테이블 전체가 브렛스키의 칩 더미가 작은 산처럼 불어나는 것을 지켜보았다. 소문이 돌기 시작했다. 그는 전직 프로 선수였고, MIT 카드 세는 사람이었으며, 한 번 돌리면 코르벳을 따낸 적도 있었다.

그는 룰렛으로 바꿔 검은색에 10만 달러를 걸었다. 공이 돌았다. 빨간색이었다.

움찔하지 않고 돈을 두 배로 올렸다. 다시 검은색이었다. 다시 빨간색이었다.

관중은 조용해졌다. 그러고 나서 그는 펠트 위로 돈을 전부 밀어 넣었다.

"100만 달러. 17번에."

숨이 찼다.

영업 사원은 침을 꿀꺽 삼켰다. 공이 돌았다.

"자, 행운의 숫자 17번..." 브렛스키가 속삭였다.

바퀴가 느려졌다. 찰칵, 찰칵, 찰칵... 17번. 그곳은 폭발했다.

그가 축하하기도 전에 두 명의 경비원이 그의 옆에 섰다. 세 번째 경비원이 그에게 전화기를 건넸다.

"누군가 당신과 이야기하고 싶어 합니다." 경비원이 엄숙하게 말했다.

브렛스키는 얼굴을 찡그렸다. "누구?"

수화기 너머에서 거친 목소리가 들려왔다. *"다시는 도박하지 말라고 했잖아, 브렛. 방금 계약이 발동된 거야."*

"무슨 계약?"

하지만 전화가 끊겼다. 불빛이 깜빡였다. 딜러는 사라졌고, 칩도 사라졌다.

그리고 그의 주변 카지노는 침묵에 휩싸였다.

#슬롯 #블랙잭 #도박 #카지노 #바카라 #룰렛

nl-NL.description:
We zijn terug in het casino en doen iets speciaals voor me. Gate City Casino heeft EINDELIJK hun kleine limieten voor tafelspellen opgeheven... dus je weet dat het tijd is om te gaan! Heel erg bedankt voor het liken, abonneren en het achterlaten van je mening in de reacties. Zelfs als je me belachelijk maakt, hou ik nog steeds van jullie. Jullie zijn allemaal prachtig en ik waardeer het enorm dat jullie allemaal mee hebben gedaan aan deze gekke reis. Wens me succes en ik zie jullie bij de volgende! Laten we ten strijde trekken.
leeg.

Als je gokkasten en tafelspellen wilt spelen, helemaal gratis en in meer dan 40 staten, klik dan op deze link hieronder en speel vandaag nog op Spin Quest. Of stem af op een livestream. Ik ben de meeste weekdagen live op Spin Quest! https://spinquest.com/?u=brettski

Brettski paradeerde over de parkeerplaats van Gate City Casino, terwijl de neonflits op zijn zonnebril met spiegelende glazen weerkaatste. Het was zijn eerste bezoek sinds ze de inzetlimieten op tafelspellen hadden afgeschaft, en hij voelde de verandering in de lucht – gespannen, elektrisch geladen, als de momenten voor een zomerstorm.

Binnen trilde de sfeer van energie. High rollers in maatpakken nipten aan bourbon naast studenten met omgekeerde hoeden. Brettski liep recht naar de blackjacktafel, waar de dealer, een vrouw met een zilveren streep in haar haar en een uit steen gehouwen pokerface, één keer knikte. Hij gooide een kraakheldere tienduizend.

"Hit me," zei hij.

Aas.

"Nog een."

Negen.

"Blijf."

De dealer gooide. Twintig. Push.

Een warming-up.

Hij verhoogde. Twintigduizend. Vijftig. Al snel keek de hele tafel toe hoe Brettski's stapel fiches groeide als een kleine berg. De geruchten begonnen te circuleren – hij was een ex-prof, een MIT-kaartenteller, een man die ooit een Corvette had gewonnen met één draai.

Hij stapte over op roulette en zette $100.000 in op zwart. De bal draaide. Rood.

Geen spier. Hij verdubbelde. Weer zwart. Weer rood.

Het publiek werd stil. Toen schoof hij zijn hele bankroll over het vilt.

"Een miljoen. Op zeventien."

Hij hapte naar adem.

De croupier slikte moeizaam. De bal draaide.

"Kom op, geluksgetal zeventien..." fluisterde Brettski.

Het wiel vertraagde. Klik-klik-klik... zeventien. De zaak ontplofte.

Voordat hij kon juichen, kwamen er twee bewakers naast hem staan. Een derde gaf hem een telefoon.

"Iemand wil je spreken," zei de bewaker grimmig.

Brettski fronste. "Wie?"

Een schorre stem aan de andere kant: *"Ik zei toch dat je nooit meer moest gokken, Brett. Je hebt net het contract geactiveerd."*

"Welk contract?"

Maar de lijn viel uit. De lichten flikkerden. De dealer was weg. De fiches waren verdwenen.

En overal om hem heen werd het stil in het casino.

snippet.title: Future Games Show at gamescom 2025
snippet.description:
The Future Games Show at gamescom starts at 11am PDT / 2pm EDT / 7pm BST / 8pm CEST / 2am CST* on Wednesday, August 20. The digital showcase will be broadcast on Twitch, YouTube, X, TikTok, GamesRadar, BiliBili, ESR and more.

But that’s not all - for the first time ever, three shows will air as part of our gamescom event schedule. This year’s Future Games Show at gamescom is immediately followed by FGS Live from gamescom. This expansion showcase is hosted by FGS channel presenters Jules and Nathan, and will provide even more wishlist-expanding gaming news and world premiere trailers.

Then, four days later on Sunday, August 24, we’ll debut a brand new format called FGS Best of gamescom. After scouring the gamescom show floor for the most unique and creative AAA, AA and indie games, the FGS team will help viewers discover something new with exclusive gameplay demos, booth tours and insight-loaded developer interviews. You can see the 'best of' the four-day gamescom event in a little under an hour during our special broadcast.

https://www.youtube.com/@FutureGamesShow

#FutureGamesShow #FGS

Future Publishing uses the Epidemic Sound Library, Getty Image Library, Shutterstock Image Library, Motion Array and Adobe Creative Cloud

snippet.title: Starting Over as NOOB with Secret Los Hotspotsitos in Steal a Brainrot!
snippet.description:
Starting Over as NOOB with Secret Los Hotspotsitos in Steal a Brainrot!

Socials:
Profile: https://www.roblox.com/users/8607372228/profile
Community: https://www.roblox.com/share/g/36097648

--

What is Roblox? ROBLOX is an online virtual playground and workshop, where kids of all ages can safely interact, create, have fun, and learn. It’s unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 13 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX — interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything — be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer “Capture the Flag” game or some other, yet-to-be-dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (“Robux”). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

#Roblox

snippet.title: Real mountains in Minecraft
snippet.description:
I wanted to see what some real mountains would look like in Minecraft so I imported elevation data into the game and talk a bit about the different types.

Here is a link to the Teton World also. Its a beast to run. You will need 6 gigs of ram allocated to minecraft and distant horizons to see that far. If you are using distant horizons, i recommend letting it just sit there and generate the distant terrain before trying to explore. This world hard crashed my PC several times and its a pretty decent PC. I probably won't keep this link up forever since the world is on the bigger size. So, if you are from the future, I'm sorry.

snippet.title: Creating Custom POKEMON for YOU! (Episode 37)
snippet.description:
In this series we use the power of random wheels to get factors for a Pokémon that we then CREATE just for you!
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Socials:
Discord: https://discord.gg/gvAE9TjvpR
2nd Channel: https://youtube.com/@Void_Fillers?si=MF8xWAiYrHx5rcd8
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/pokedex_fillers/
Tiktok: https://www.tiktok.com/@pokedex_fillers?lang=en

Artists!
Devesa_Illustrations (Customon 1, Thumbnail Ball, & Member Mod): @devesaillustrations 
MathDex12 (Customon 2): https://www.instagram.com/poketrainervb/
ThePanio (Customon 3): @ThePanio_ 

Music: 
All music is by  @The_Zame  !
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_IxBpEinqYw&list=PPSV
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NTHnkxwFgWE&list=RDNTHnkxwFgWE&start_radio=1
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1L-pwaH4mtg&list=RDNTHnkxwFgWE&index=2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7ZZyuIouSuk&list=RD7ZZyuIouSuk&start_radio=1
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z0LyWQ_gNzE&list=RDZ0LyWQ_gNzE&start_radio=1

AI Usage
As you may have noticed I do use AI to generate backgrounds and some other simple aspects for the animations describing the Custom Pokémon such as generating an image of a forest to put the Pokémon walking around in as a simple example. The Pokémon themselves are always commissioned from artists (found above) and my reasoning for using AI is it is simply the most effective way to accomplish the goal of this series which is to bring to life the Fakemon myself and the team of artist have made for YOU while telling fun stories.

snippet.title: These Tanks NEED To Be Nerfed
snippet.description:
War Thunder has a habit of making anti-aircraft tanks better as tank destroyers than counters to CAS planes, but 35mm SPAA like the Za-35 and XM246 take it to a completely different level. I took both of them to top tier where they are still very competitive, and we came close to getting a few nukes.

Check the channel "About" section for the link to the creator of my profile picture.
